  "local_port": 45548,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you say goodbye to a dying loved one?",
  "response": "Saying goodbye to a dying loved one is one of the most difficult and emotionally charged experiences anyone can face. There is no \"right\" or \"wrong\" way to approach it, as everyone\u2019s journey is unique. However, here are some suggestions to help guide you during this deeply personal moment:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Be Present**\n   - Simply being with them can be the most meaningful gesture. Your physical presence can provide comfort and reassurance.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Express Your Love**\n   - Tell them how much they mean to you. Say \"I love you\" or share specific memories that highlight their impact on your life.\n   - Example: \"I love you so much, and I\u2019ll always remember the way you made me laugh.\"\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Acknowledge Their Life**\n   - Thank them for the role they\u2019ve played in your life. Acknowledge their contributions, kindness, and love.\n   - Example: \"Thank you for everything you\u2019ve done for me. You\u2019ve shaped who I am, and I\u2019m so grateful.\"\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Offer Forgiveness (if needed)**\n   - If there are unresolved issues or hurts, consider offering forgiveness or seeking it from them. This can bring peace to both of you.\n   - Example: \"I forgive you for everything, and I hope you can forgive me, too.\"\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Reassure Them**\n   - Let them know it\u2019s okay to let go. Reassure them that you and others will be okay, even though it\u2019s hard.\n   - Example: \"You\u2019ve fought so hard, and it\u2019s okay to rest now. We\u2019ll be okay, and we\u2019ll keep your memory alive.\"\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Listen and Be Silent**\n   - If they\u2019re able to speak, listen to what they have to say. Sometimes, silence and holding their hand can be more powerful than words.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Share Gratitude**\n   - Express gratitude for the time you\u2019ve had together and the lessons they\u2019ve taught you.\n   - Example: \"I\u2019m so thankful for all the moments we shared. You\u2019ve taught me so much about love and resilience.\"\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Offer Spiritual Comfort (if appropriate)**\n   - If they have spiritual beliefs, you can pray with them, read meaningful texts, or offer words of comfort aligned with their faith.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Allow Yourself to Feel**\n   - It\u2019s okay to cry, to feel sadness, or even to feel numb. Your emotions are valid, and expressing them can be healing.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Remember They Are Still There**\n   - Even if they are unresponsive, they may still be able to hear or sense your presence. Continue speaking to them or holding their hand.\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Take Care of Yourself**\n   - Grieving is a process, and it\u2019s important to be gentle with yourself afterward. Seek support from friends, family, or a counselor.\n\n---\n\n### Final Thoughts:\nThere is no perfect way to say goodbye, but the most important thing is to speak from the heart. Your love and presence will mean more than any specific words. Cherish the time you have, and remember that goodbye is not the end\u2014it\u2019s a way to honor the bond you share.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
